Sampson Itode, Port Harcourt Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Wike, has presented a budget of N448.6bn for 2021 to the state House of Assembly. The proposed 2021 budget christened, ‘Budget of Recovery and Consolidation,’ had N305.8bn for capital expenditure, while N142.7bn was earmarked for recurrent expenditure. Wike, while presenting the budget to the lawmakers at the state assembly in Port Harcourt on Wednesday disclosed that  2021 budget represented more than 20 per cent increase above the 2020 revised budget of N300bn. The Special Assistant to the Governor on Media, Kelvin Ebiri, in a statement quoted Wike as saying that the capital expenditure, represented 68.18 per cent of the total budget size, stressing that it would be deployed to engender economic growth and social progress. Wike noted that N82.9bn had been allocated for the provision of infrastructure, including roads, bridges, and completion of flyover projects at Okoro-Nu-Odo, Rumuola, Rumuogba, and Port Harcourt GRA junction. He said, “We will also deliver the Ogoni – Andoni – Opobo unity road, the Eastern bypass dualization, 6th and 7th flyover projects and the Wakama road as well as all other ongoing rural roads in our communities and local government areas across the state.” He stated that the policy thrust for the year 2021 budget will be to accelerate economic recovery, drive growth and create opportunities for social progress; enhance human capital development and tackle poverty; building first class infrastructures to accelerate our socio-economic development. The Speaker, Rivers state House of Assembly, Ikuinyi Ibani, lauded Governor Wike’s commitment in transforming the state’s economy. Copyright PUNCH.
